The paper presents a data structure for maintaining a planar graph under edge contractions and applies it to various planar graph problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), graph theory (cs.GT), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). However, since the focus is primarily on data structures and graph algorithms, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories.
